text.tspan: Generic chart title to silence errors
Share of population by age groups suffering from any mental health or substance use disorders; this includes
depression, anxiety, bipolar, eating disorders, alcohol or drug use disorders, and schizophrenia. Due to the
widespread under-diagnosis, these estimates use a combination of sources, including medical and national records,
epidemiological data, survey data, and meta-regression models.
Source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease
